title: For Sale:  Stoeger 8000 F Cougar 9mm Pistol
postcontent: Pre-Owned Stoeger 8000F Cougar Pistols: Champions of Tactical Reliability The new Stoeger 8000 Cougar semi-auto pistols inherit the reputation of the original Beretta 8000 as reliable, durable and powerful. First designed primarily for tactical undercover work, the Cougar is now carried by a growing number of police officers as their official duty sidearm thanks to its ergonomics, low recoil and inherent accuracy. The original Beretta Cougar was NATO qualified and boasted a long service-life of more than 30,000 9mm rounds. In its new incarnation, Beretta has developed an ergonomically-advanced pistol that is compact but capable of handling high-power cartridges, offering high magazine capacity and giving a long service life. This has been possible also thanks to the innovative adaptation of a locked-breech system with a rotating barrel. Today, the new Stoeger 8000 Cougar pistol is manufactured by the Stoeger Silah Sanayi A.S., strictly in line with the most traditional Beretta quality control and attention to detail. Low Recoil Upon firing this pistol, shooters are amazed by the low felt recoil. This is due to two factors working together. The first is the rotating barrel system, which dissipates recoil radially rather than directing it into the shooter’s hand. The second is the central block, which absorbs the mechanical recoil from the barrel and the slide before this is transferred to the frame. When the Cougar is in battery, the positive lock-up of barrel to slide assures perfect alignment of barrel and sights. Upon firing, the barrel travels and rotates with axial movement. Besides low recoil, the result is superior accuracy and quicker recovery for follow-up shots. Advanced Ergonomics for Easy Handling, Control, Concealment The Cougar is one of the most ergonomically advanced pistols in its class. The user-friendly, contoured frame and grips make the Cougar exceptionally easy to control during firing. By taking hand anatomy and instinctive hold into account, the Cougar accommodates smaller hands and also protects larger hands from being bitten by the slide. All edges are rounded or beveled, and are carefully finished to make the Cougar virtually snag-proof and exceptionally easy to draw and conceal. Different Configurations to Suit Most Tactical Needs The Cougar L Type P is conceived to deliver high firepower in F or D (Double Action Only) operating systems. F models have the same safety features of the famous Beretta 92 FS pistol: external ambidextrous manual safety with decocking lever, trigger bar disconnect, rotating firing pin striker, firing pin block device and loaded-chamber indicator. The double-action-only D versions have the firing pin block device and the loaded-chamber indicator but no manual safety, thereby offering a super-smooth, exceptionally snag-free side. Both versions are manufactured in 9 mm or .40 caliber to satisfy the different needs of police officers and concealed-carry permit holders.The 8000 Cougar L 9mm pistol, available in F or D configurations, features the same rotating barrel system of the full-size Cougar L Type P; the difference is in the shortened grip frame that houses a 13-round, high-capacity double-stack magazine. The beveled slide and the reduced dimensions and weight also make this model ideal for undercover work. title: For Sale/Trade:  Gewehr Model '88' 8mm
postcontent: This old Gewehr Model '88' was actually manufactured in 1891. These rifles have a very long and colorful history, and have even been featured in the American Rifleman magazine.  These are very collectable rifles and make great conversation pieces.   By BATF rules and guidelines this very nice rifle is not considered s 'FIREARM', per se.  It is chambered in 8mm Mauser caliber, and was one of the ones which ended up in the Turkish empire.  This rifle is marked 'LOEWE BERLIN' and has Turkish markings amd 1891 stamped on the receiver.  It also has an 'S' on the receiver, which I believe means that it has been modified to shoot the modern spire shaped modern 8mm ammo, it has the proper cut outs for the bullet and also for the use of stripper clips.  This rifle has a very strong bore; but I have never shot it before, as 8mm is not one of the calibers I shoot.  This rifle is in overall outstanding condition, not at all rusty or the least bit pitted.  It has the floor plate cover, and the proper cleaning rod as well.  As an antique classified weapon, there are no selling restrictions for this rifle.  Trades will be considered.

title: For Sale:  MOSIN/NAGANT 91/30 7.62x54R  Dated 1942
postcontent: Mosin Nagant 91/30 WWII rifle dated 1942.  This is a totally 'outstanding' rifle which does not appear to have ever been rebuilt in it's lifetime.  There are a couple of mismatched serial number metal parts, but otherwise this rifle is absolutely near perfect and 'BEAUTIFUL', and has never been stored in tons of grease like most have been.  This is the very last 91/30 that I will be selling; because I 'LOVE' shooting these old historical rifles myself!  The rifle stock is just about as perfect as any stock I've ever seen on a 91/30, and it even has lots of original stock 'CARTOUCHES', and the original finish.  Most of these rifles have this horrible, and crappy looking, colored sloppy laquer applied to the stock; which comes off very easily.   There is absolutely no rust or pitting anywhere on this beauty!  This comes with a bayonet {not serial matched} ammo pouches which contain the grease and oil bottle, wrench, and cleaning kit.  This also has a sling which is an AK-47 sling, but still very nice.  I am not including ammo in this sale; but I am willing to sell quite a bit of it to whomever will buy this very nice rifle.  By the way, I have shot this rifle, and it is very accurate shooting.  My buddy and I love to put scrap pieces of wood on the 50 yard berm and literally 'BLOW THEM TO PIECES'!!  This rifle is C&R eligible, so even out of state buyers with that license are eligible to purchase this.  Otherwise this rifle can only be sold to Alabama residents who are at least 18 years of age  I have been selling at local Dothan gun shows forever; but now am geting too crippled up to do that any longer.   Very soon I will be listing a lot of my old gun show show items on Armslist in an effort to sell it all off.  Included will be ammo cans, knives, bayonets, dummy grenades, lots of rifle and pistol ammo, etc., etc.!!!  Please call me at 334=671-8550 for additional info.
